  "summary": "Spawning bug",
  "environment_raw": null,
  "description": "In the first wave, pillagers spawned on an island beside the village and were completely passive, and the captain dropped an ominous bottle n n n n",
  "Steps to Reproduce": "1. Create a new Survival world with default settings.\n2. Locate or create a village with at least one villager and one claimed bed.\n3. Obtain the Bad Omen effect by killing a raid captain or drinking an Ominous Potion.\n4. Enter the village while still affected by the Bad Omen effect to trigger a raid.\n5. Observe the first wave of pillagers spawning near the village.\n6. Note the location where the pillagers spawn; they should appear on an island adjacent to the village.\n7. Check the behavior of the spawned pillagers; they should remain completely passive and not attack.\n8. Identify the pillager captain among the spawned pillagers and confirm that it drops an Ominous Bottle upon defeat.",
  "Environment": "Minecraft Java Edition Version 1.21.8",
  "Observed Behavior": "During the first wave of a raid, pillagers spawned on an island adjacent to the village instead of within the village boundaries. Notably, these pillagers exhibited passive behavior, failing to engage with the player or the villagers, which is inconsistent with their typical aggressive nature during a raid. Additionally, the raid captain among them dropped an ominous bottle upon defeat. The drop of the ominous bottle is standard behavior for a raid captain; however, the passive state of the pillagers during the raid contradicts expected mechanics, as they should actively attack players and villagers when a raid is triggered by a player with the Bad Omen effect entering the village. This discrepancy raises concerns regarding the spawning logic and behavioral triggers for pillagers in this specific scenario.",
  "Expected Behavior": "In the first wave of a raid, pillagers should spawn within the designated raid area surrounding the village, displaying their hostile behavior and actively seeking out villagers to attack. The raid captain, which is typically a pillager, should also spawn alongside the other pillagers, equipped with an ominous banner. Upon defeat, this captain should drop an ominous banner and potentially other loot, such as arrows or a crossbow, depending on the game's loot mechanics. The pillagers should not be passive; instead, they should engage in attacking villagers and attempting to break down doors or cause chaos within the village, consistent with the intended behavior of illagers during a raid event.",
